
---


@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes and methods

class User {
    +String name
    +String email
}

class Student {
    +makeRequest()
    +browseTutoringOffers()
    +payForSession()
}

class Tutor {
    +String bankAccount
    +offerTutoring()
    +updateAvailability()
    +confirmOrRescheduleSession()
    +receivePayment()
}

class Session {
    +DateTime scheduledTime
    +float price
    +String subject
    +int level
    +boolean confirmed
    +scheduleFollowUp()
    +cancelSession()
}

class Subject {
    +String name
}

class Level {
    +String description // e.g., "Primary School", "High School"
}

class Availability {
    +Day day
    +Time startTime
    +Time endTime
}

class Payment {
    +String method // e.g., Credit Card, Wire Transfer
    +processPayment()
}

class Award {
    +Date awardMonth
    +Subject subject
    +Tutor tutor
}

' Inheritance
User <|-- Student
User <|-- Tutor

' Associations
Tutor "1" --> "many" Subject : offers tutoring in
Tutor "1" --> "many" Availability : has availability
Tutor "1" --> "many" Session : conducts session
Student "1" --> "many" Session : attends session
Session "1" --> "1" Subject : related to
Session "1" --> "1" Level : at level
Session "1" --> "1" Payment : payment for
Tutor "1" --> "many" Award : awarded as tutor of the month

' Additional associations
Student "1" --> "many" Session : makes requests for
Tutor "1" --> "many" Session : receives requests for

@enduml

---

### 🔍 Notes on the Diagram:

- **User** is an abstract base class from which **Student** and **Tutor** inherit.
- **Tutor** can offer tutoring in multiple subjects at different levels with specific hourly rates.
- **Student** can make requests and browse available sessions.
- **Session** connects a **Student** and a **Tutor**, includes scheduling, pricing, and cancellation logic.
- **Availability** defines when a tutor is available.
- **Payment** handles how students pay after the session.
- **Award** tracks monthly best tutors per subject.

